article.headline: Stanford 60, Washington St. 58
article.story: STANFORD, Calif. -- Jeremy Green scored 18 of his 24 points in the second half, including the game-winner with 4.6 seconds left, as Stanford rallied from an 18-point deficit Thursday to beat Washington State 60-58. Landry Fields added 15 points for the Cardinal (11-13, 5-7 Pac-10), who trailed 44-26 with just over 10 minutes remaining to play. Klay Thompson scored 19 points for the Cougars (15-9, 5-7 Pac-10), who lost their fourth in five games. DeAngelo Casto added 15 points and 10 rebounds. Stanford remains the only undefeated team at home in Pac-10 Conference play. It had lost four straight road games but avoided its longest losing streak in 17 years by outscoring the Cougars 17-6 over the final six minutes.
